1
00:01:08,300 --> 00:01:10,800
"Blue Lips"

2
00:01:11,200 --> 00:01:13,700
(Episode 7)

3
00:01:29,960 --> 00:01:30,960
Stop right there.

4
00:01:31,920 --> 00:01:32,920
Sis.

5
00:01:33,719 --> 00:01:34,719
Come here.

6
00:01:39,980 --> 00:01:41,980
I knew you were acting
sneaky these past few days.

7
00:01:42,619 --> 00:01:44,499
And sure enough, you
sneak back in the morning.

8
00:01:46,860 --> 00:01:48,699
The bar has been too busy lately.

9
00:01:50,280 --> 00:01:51,280
Liar.

10
00:01:54,500 --> 00:01:56,000
I called your boss.

11
00:01:56,400 --> 00:01:57,460
He said you left ages ago.

12
00:01:58,119 --> 00:01:59,300
Who exactly did you go see?

13
00:02:02,039 --> 00:02:02,440
I...

14
00:02:02,699 --> 00:02:03,739
I'm really not lying, Sis.

15
00:02:04,179 --> 00:02:05,320
I drank too much yesterday.

16
00:02:05,579 --> 00:02:06,980
And I missed the last bus.

17
00:02:07,079 --> 00:02:08,719
So I crashed at my bandmate's place.

18
00:02:09,000 --> 00:02:10,000
Really.

19
00:02:10,079 --> 00:02:11,436
If you don't believe me,
I'll give you his number.

20
00:02:11,460 --> 00:02:12,460
You can ask him yourself.

21
00:02:16,112 --> 00:02:17,112
Really?

22
00:02:18,079 --> 00:02:19,079
Really.

23
00:02:22,559 --> 00:02:24,039
I'll take your word for it this time.

24
00:02:25,719 --> 00:02:26,719
Okay.

25
00:02:27,000 --> 00:02:28,380
Sis, I'm going in then.

26
00:02:29,000 --> 00:02:30,000
Stop right there.

27
00:02:31,159 --> 00:02:32,159
Come back.

28
00:02:38,619 --> 00:02:39,719
I have some good news.

29
00:02:40,380 --> 00:02:42,140
The doctor said my
vitals are under control.

30
00:02:42,340 --> 00:02:43,500
Once my condition stabilizes,

31
00:02:43,760 --> 00:02:45,300
you can quit your job at Blue Moon.

32
00:02:45,480 --> 00:02:46,820
And I can go back to work.

33
00:02:47,679 --> 00:02:48,280
Our lives

34
00:02:48,559 --> 00:02:50,119
will finally get back on track.

35
00:02:53,539 --> 00:02:54,779
With you working at a place like Blue Moon,

36
00:02:54,780 --> 00:02:55,980
I can never really be at ease.

37
00:02:56,900 --> 00:02:58,159
It's fine. At the bar,

38
00:02:58,780 --> 00:02:59,880
I know my limits.

39
00:03:01,739 --> 00:03:02,739
Go on.

40
00:03:04,380 --> 00:03:05,519
Stop drinking from now on.

41
00:03:06,119 --> 00:03:07,119
Got it, Sis.

42
00:03:28,579 --> 00:03:29,579
Looking sharp.

43
00:03:31,619 --> 00:03:32,939
You even coordinated your outfit.

44
00:03:38,780 --> 00:03:39,780
Is this...

45
00:03:45,440 --> 00:03:46,440
Do I look bad?

46
00:03:46,960 --> 00:03:48,400
You think it looks sharp too, right?

47
00:03:50,980 --> 00:03:51,619
Look at Brother Mo.

48
00:03:51,800 --> 00:03:53,000
Even he thinks it looks sharp.

49
00:03:54,300 --> 00:03:55,580
Strutting around like a peacock.

50
00:03:56,159 --> 00:03:57,360
I have to ask,

51
00:03:57,559 --> 00:03:59,340
is that a compliment or an insult?

52
00:03:59,659 --> 00:04:00,880
Definitely a compliment.

53
00:04:01,099 --> 00:04:02,539
Ask Xiao Wu if you don't believe me.

54
00:04:04,239 --> 00:04:05,239
What do you think?

55
00:04:05,500 --> 00:04:06,619
Does it look bad?

56
00:04:10,219 --> 00:04:11,379
You look better than a model.

57
00:04:12,519 --> 00:04:13,619
Really?

58
00:04:17,539 --> 00:04:17,940
Oh, right.

59
00:04:18,280 --> 00:04:19,400
The money from last time,

60
00:04:19,719 --> 00:04:21,155
I should have transferred it to you.

61
00:04:21,179 --> 00:04:22,039
I just sent it over.

62
00:04:22,159 --> 00:04:22,500
Also,

63
00:04:22,599 --> 00:04:24,360
I transferred today's share as well.

64
00:04:25,239 --> 00:04:26,239
Check it.

65
00:04:31,860 --> 00:04:32,860
What are you doing here?

66
00:04:32,940 --> 00:04:34,880
Only you intellectuals are
allowed here? We can't come?

67
00:04:36,119 --> 00:04:36,719
Are you insulting me?

68
00:04:36,743 --> 00:04:37,403
[Sister calling]

69
00:04:38,179 --> 00:04:39,139
Looking so flashy today.
Having a second youth?

70
00:04:39,139 --> 00:04:39,860
Hey, I'm working.

71
00:04:39,860 --> 00:04:40,860
The stuff at home...

72
00:04:43,760 --> 00:04:44,816
Let's grab a couple of drinks.

73
00:04:44,840 --> 00:04:45,840
Ah Heng.

74
00:04:46,280 --> 00:04:47,400
Pour us two drinks.

75
00:04:50,880 --> 00:04:51,880
Brother Hao.

76
00:04:53,960 --> 00:04:54,559
Let's talk outside.

77
00:04:54,559 --> 00:04:54,880
Okay.

78
00:04:55,500 --> 00:04:56,019
Something came up.

79
00:04:56,340 --> 00:04:57,340
I'll be right back.

80
00:04:58,920 --> 00:04:59,920
See you in a bit.

81
00:05:04,780 --> 00:05:05,780
Hey, handsome.

82
00:05:07,179 --> 00:05:09,380
Mind if I sit next to you for a while?

83
00:05:10,639 --> 00:05:11,639
I do mind.

84
00:05:13,639 --> 00:05:15,380
Don't be so stingy.

85
00:05:19,760 --> 00:05:20,780
To be honest,

86
00:05:21,159 --> 00:05:23,280
I love a gentleman.

87
00:05:24,139 --> 00:05:25,380
Whenever I meet one,

88
00:05:25,820 --> 00:05:27,239
I don't want to miss out.

89
00:05:29,360 --> 00:05:30,600
Let's add each other on WeChat.

90
00:05:32,559 --> 00:05:33,559
I don't think

91
00:05:34,300 --> 00:05:35,400
that's necessary.

92
00:05:36,699 --> 00:05:37,699
What's wrong?

93
00:05:38,320 --> 00:05:40,019
Do you not like curly hair,

94
00:05:40,619 --> 00:05:42,059
or do you just not like

95
00:05:42,840 --> 00:05:43,840
me?

96
00:05:45,420 --> 00:05:46,420
I...

97
00:05:47,699 --> 00:05:48,699
Right.

98
00:05:49,079 --> 00:05:50,360
He doesn't like you.

99
00:05:51,219 --> 00:05:51,619
Brother Heng.

100
00:05:51,780 --> 00:05:53,660
Something came up
today, so I won't be singing.

101
00:05:55,800 --> 00:05:56,960
What's that supposed to mean?

102
00:06:02,199 --> 00:06:03,199
I need a room.

103
00:06:03,780 --> 00:06:04,860
Okay, please wait a moment.

104
00:06:09,300 --> 00:06:10,300
All set.

105
00:07:15,260 --> 00:07:16,260
What are you doing?

106
00:07:16,320 --> 00:07:17,320
Interrogating me?

107
00:07:17,480 --> 00:07:18,480
Cut the crap.

108
00:07:19,400 --> 00:07:20,400
Tell me the truth.

109
00:07:20,760 --> 00:07:22,240
What were you talking about just now?

110
00:07:22,340 --> 00:07:23,900
Age, family income,

111
00:07:24,659 --> 00:07:25,559
when to get married,

112
00:07:25,639 --> 00:07:27,099
even picked out the kids' names.

113
00:07:30,900 --> 00:07:31,900
That hurts!

114
00:07:33,219 --> 00:07:34,800
Do you have any professional ethics?

115
00:07:36,119 --> 00:07:37,379
When you're with me,

116
00:07:37,380 --> 00:07:38,980
you're not allowed to flirt with others.

117
00:07:39,039 --> 00:07:40,199
She was flirting with me!

118
00:07:41,000 --> 00:07:42,340
That makes it even worse.

119
00:07:46,400 --> 00:07:46,719
Teng Mo!

120
00:07:46,960 --> 00:07:47,960
Teng Mo!

121
00:07:58,559 --> 00:07:59,699
Teng Mo, what are you doing?

122
00:08:03,780 --> 00:08:04,780
Teng Mo!

123
00:08:37,600 --> 00:08:38,680
Pervert!

124
00:08:50,319 --> 00:08:51,319
I'm a pervert?

125
00:08:52,340 --> 00:08:53,340
You don't like it?

126
00:08:54,520 --> 00:08:55,819
Stop talking.

127
00:08:56,060 --> 00:08:56,560
Fine.

128
00:08:56,659 --> 00:08:57,659
Let's continue then.

129
00:09:04,539 --> 00:09:05,060
Teng Mo!

130
00:09:05,539 --> 00:09:06,539
Teng Mo!

131
00:09:07,579 --> 00:09:08,579
What did you call me?

132
00:09:10,979 --> 00:09:11,979
Brother Mo.

133
00:09:12,479 --> 00:09:13,479
Wrong.

134
00:09:14,760 --> 00:09:15,760
Brother.

135
00:09:16,899 --> 00:09:17,899
Say it again.

136
00:09:18,640 --> 00:09:19,779
Brother, Brother.

137
00:09:20,539 --> 00:09:21,539
Brother.

138
00:09:21,899 --> 00:09:22,899
Brother.

139
00:09:32,159 --> 00:09:33,159
Brother.

140
00:09:36,680 --> 00:09:37,680
Teng Mo.

141
00:10:12,319 --> 00:10:13,579
You know what, Shixian?

142
00:10:15,779 --> 00:10:17,920
You look especially cute today.

143
00:10:38,640 --> 00:10:39,720
You're so energetic today.

144
00:10:40,340 --> 00:10:41,720
Did you take Vandacon?

145
00:10:46,819 --> 00:10:48,779
I only take it when I'm
with people I don't like.

146
00:10:50,560 --> 00:10:51,819
So you like me.

147
00:10:53,659 --> 00:10:54,920
As if I'd like you.

148
00:10:59,079 --> 00:11:00,680
There's no need to be jealous of others.

149
00:11:02,159 --> 00:11:03,279
I only like you.

150
00:11:28,319 --> 00:11:29,319
Shixian.

151
00:11:30,279 --> 00:11:31,759
Do you have time these next few days?

152
00:11:33,000 --> 00:11:34,000
Why?

153
00:11:34,720 --> 00:11:35,720
The seasons are changing.

154
00:11:35,760 --> 00:11:36,319
I wanted you

155
00:11:36,500 --> 00:11:37,940
to come with me to buy some clothes.

156
00:11:40,180 --> 00:11:41,180
Tomorrow...

157
00:11:41,600 --> 00:11:42,739
I might not be free.

158
00:11:43,180 --> 00:11:44,180
How about Sunday?

159
00:11:44,520 --> 00:11:45,020
Sure.

160
00:11:45,420 --> 00:11:46,939
We'll go whenever you're free.

161
00:11:47,760 --> 00:11:49,060
Sunday it is.

162
00:11:51,039 --> 00:11:52,116
Is there anything you want?

163
00:11:52,140 --> 00:11:53,620
Or anything you want to gift someone?

164
00:11:54,600 --> 00:11:55,060
No.

165
00:11:55,460 --> 00:11:56,460
I...

166
00:11:57,340 --> 00:11:58,780
I don't have anything I want to buy.

167
00:11:59,079 --> 00:12:00,739
And no one to buy gifts for.

168
00:12:02,899 --> 00:12:03,899
All right.

169
00:12:31,359 --> 00:12:32,439
Have you been waiting long?

170
00:12:38,859 --> 00:12:40,020
Why are you staring at me?

171
00:12:42,979 --> 00:12:43,359
Nothing.

172
00:12:43,500 --> 00:12:45,199
It just feels like the first time

173
00:12:45,300 --> 00:12:46,820
I've hung out with you during the day.

174
00:12:47,500 --> 00:12:48,520
It feels like a dream.

175
00:12:49,199 --> 00:12:50,939
Don't exaggerate so much.

176
00:12:53,960 --> 00:12:54,960
That store looks nice.

177
00:12:55,119 --> 00:12:56,119
Let's go take a look.

178
00:12:56,840 --> 00:12:57,840
That one?

179
00:12:58,359 --> 00:12:59,359
Are you sure?

180
00:12:59,779 --> 00:13:00,939
We're already here. Let's go.

181
00:14:04,600 --> 00:14:05,600
It's fine, try again.

182
00:14:15,500 --> 00:14:15,960
What is it?

183
00:14:16,199 --> 00:14:17,279
Do you like this necklace?

184
00:14:18,260 --> 00:14:18,720
No.

185
00:14:18,859 --> 00:14:19,859
Just browsing.

186
00:14:20,159 --> 00:14:21,159
Let's go.

187
00:14:21,899 --> 00:14:23,555
Your neck is definitely missing something.

188
00:14:23,579 --> 00:14:24,579
Why don't we buy it?

189
00:14:26,260 --> 00:14:27,840
I'm really just browsing.

190
00:14:28,260 --> 00:14:29,856
Didn't you say you wanted me to treat you?

191
00:14:29,880 --> 00:14:30,880
Have you decided?

192
00:14:32,539 --> 00:14:33,539
I...

193
00:14:34,300 --> 00:14:35,420
Treat me to some ice cream.

194
00:14:36,039 --> 00:14:36,420
Sure.

195
00:14:36,720 --> 00:14:37,720
Let's go.

196
00:14:44,340 --> 00:14:46,140
With all the money I
usually transfer to you,

197
00:14:46,239 --> 00:14:47,819
I never see you buy any decent clothes.

198
00:14:48,399 --> 00:14:50,156
You just wear the same
few outfits over and over.

199
00:14:50,180 --> 00:14:50,979
Aren't you tired of them?

200
00:14:51,079 --> 00:14:52,639
The audience must be tired of them too.

201
00:14:53,039 --> 00:14:55,399
Didn't the boss at Blue Moon
give you a clothing allowance?

202
00:14:56,020 --> 00:14:57,380
What clothing allowance?

203
00:14:58,920 --> 00:14:59,380
Alright.

204
00:14:59,760 --> 00:15:01,880
I'll cover your clothes from now on.

205
00:15:02,180 --> 00:15:03,539
I can handle that much.

206
00:15:06,520 --> 00:15:08,560
You always tell me not
to sing at Blue Moon,

207
00:15:09,199 --> 00:15:10,639
but now you're spending money on me,

208
00:15:10,680 --> 00:15:12,460
buying me all these clothes to support me.

209
00:15:15,079 --> 00:15:16,279
Singing at Blue Moon...

210
00:15:16,520 --> 00:15:18,079
That's just a hobby.

211
00:15:18,300 --> 00:15:19,819
Even though I don't support it,

212
00:15:19,920 --> 00:15:21,579
I'm not completely against it either.

213
00:15:22,119 --> 00:15:22,960
But you're so young,

214
00:15:23,079 --> 00:15:24,356
and you're drinking and doing drugs.

215
00:15:24,380 --> 00:15:25,380
That's not okay.

216
00:15:27,279 --> 00:15:28,819
What drinking and doing drugs?

217
00:15:29,380 --> 00:15:30,979
I just go to Blue Moon to sing.

218
00:15:32,260 --> 00:15:33,659
Alright, alright, just to sing.

219
00:15:55,840 --> 00:15:56,840
Ultimately,

220
00:15:57,579 --> 00:15:59,640
he still wants to find
a girl to marry, right?

221
00:16:01,960 --> 00:16:02,960
Looks good.

222
00:16:09,500 --> 00:16:10,119
It's nothing.

223
00:16:10,279 --> 00:16:11,279
Let's go.

224
00:16:30,220 --> 00:16:31,620
Are you sure you don't need a ride?

225
00:16:32,000 --> 00:16:33,000
No need.

226
00:16:34,239 --> 00:16:34,619
Alright.

227
00:16:34,960 --> 00:16:36,300
Then this is it. Here.

228
00:16:39,020 --> 00:16:40,020
All for me?

229
00:16:40,380 --> 00:16:41,380
Of course.

230
00:16:43,359 --> 00:16:44,359
With our relationship,

231
00:16:44,659 --> 00:16:46,339
it's only right that I spend money on you.

232
00:16:47,220 --> 00:16:48,220
A relationship...

233
00:16:48,479 --> 00:16:49,479
built on money?

234
00:16:51,619 --> 00:16:52,619
Got it.

235
00:16:54,279 --> 00:16:56,100
Next time you perform,

236
00:16:56,300 --> 00:16:57,939
remember to wear your new clothes.

237
00:17:01,500 --> 00:17:02,500
I'm off.

238
00:17:10,180 --> 00:17:11,180
You're back.

239
00:17:15,699 --> 00:17:16,840
You bought so much stuff.

240
00:17:17,180 --> 00:17:18,300
Where did you get the money?

241
00:17:20,560 --> 00:17:22,040
The boss gave me a clothing allowance

242
00:17:22,420 --> 00:17:23,539
to get a new look.

243
00:17:27,199 --> 00:17:28,199
Are you upset?

244
00:17:29,779 --> 00:17:30,779
No.

245
00:17:31,140 --> 00:17:33,340
I'm just a bit tired lately.

246
00:17:38,520 --> 00:17:39,520
Go get some rest.

247
00:18:16,979 --> 00:18:18,699
Why hasn't today's performance started yet?

248
00:18:19,399 --> 00:18:20,399
Xiao Wu got held up.

249
00:18:20,600 --> 00:18:21,600
It'll start a bit late.

250
00:18:22,479 --> 00:18:23,479
What happened to him?

251
00:18:23,819 --> 00:18:25,619
He couldn't make it in
time from his day job.

252
00:18:25,659 --> 00:18:26,779
He found a new part-time gig

253
00:18:27,739 --> 00:18:28,739
as a tutor.

254
00:18:29,859 --> 00:18:30,859
You didn't know?

255
00:18:31,439 --> 00:18:32,439
No.

256
00:18:33,340 --> 00:18:35,140
He doesn't usually
report his schedule to me.

257
00:18:37,319 --> 00:18:38,520
He's still a college student?

258
00:18:40,199 --> 00:18:42,199
Seeing how edgy he looks on stage...

259
00:18:42,680 --> 00:18:44,720
He was the top scorer in
the college entrance exam.

260
00:18:45,399 --> 00:18:46,399
That impressive?

261
00:18:46,819 --> 00:18:48,340
So he goes to college in Jinyang?

262
00:18:49,359 --> 00:18:50,359
He dropped out.

263
00:18:50,720 --> 00:18:51,880
He's in a rush to make money.

264
00:18:54,180 --> 00:18:55,340
He's that desperate for cash?

265
00:18:56,199 --> 00:18:57,300
I wouldn't know about that.

266
00:18:57,399 --> 00:18:58,679
You'll have to ask him yourself.

267
00:19:00,539 --> 00:19:01,159
Anyway,

268
00:19:01,160 --> 00:19:02,200
it's his private business.

269
00:19:02,460 --> 00:19:03,616
If he doesn't want to talk about it,

270
00:19:03,640 --> 00:19:04,680
it's not our place to ask.

271
00:19:06,960 --> 00:19:07,960
But I think

272
00:19:08,800 --> 00:19:10,040
he really is strapped for cash.

273
00:19:12,420 --> 00:19:14,319
Look at all the part-time jobs he works.

274
00:19:15,039 --> 00:19:16,679
The thing is, he hardly spends any money.

275
00:19:20,579 --> 00:19:21,579
Well, for a guy,

276
00:19:21,760 --> 00:19:23,640
needing money usually
comes down to two things.

277
00:19:24,260 --> 00:19:25,260
Either he's sick,

278
00:19:25,819 --> 00:19:26,819
or he's getting married.

279
00:19:30,159 --> 00:19:30,819
I'm at work.

280
00:19:30,819 --> 00:19:31,819
The stuff at home...

281
00:19:36,500 --> 00:19:38,159
I was really just browsing.

282
00:19:46,180 --> 00:19:46,739
Sorry.

283
00:19:47,159 --> 00:19:48,159
I'm late.

284
00:19:48,600 --> 00:19:49,279
Hurry up and get ready.

285
00:19:49,619 --> 00:19:50,779
Don't be this late next time.

286
00:19:51,180 --> 00:19:52,180
Got it.

287
00:19:53,159 --> 00:19:54,159
Pretty handsome.

288
00:20:20,640 --> 00:20:21,640
Yeah.

289
00:20:21,939 --> 00:20:22,939
And still young.

290
00:20:24,000 --> 00:20:25,478
At the very least, he
should have the chance

291
00:20:25,479 --> 00:20:28,340
to see the woman he loves
wear a wedding dress for him.

292
00:20:57,579 --> 00:20:58,699
You've got the wrong person.

293
00:20:59,000 --> 00:21:00,000
I told you,

294
00:21:00,159 --> 00:21:02,079
I have no idea what you're talking about.

295
00:21:02,279 --> 00:21:03,460
I couldn't be mistaken.

296
00:21:04,140 --> 00:21:05,920
He has the same blue lip balm as you.

297
00:21:06,439 --> 00:21:07,939
Were you two together yesterday?

298
00:21:08,239 --> 00:21:09,300
Did you sleep together?

299
00:21:10,680 --> 00:21:11,680
Let go.

300
00:21:14,000 --> 00:21:14,699
I told you,

301
00:21:14,939 --> 00:21:16,159
I'm not interested in men.

302
00:21:35,760 --> 00:21:36,760
Ah Heng.

303
00:21:36,939 --> 00:21:37,939
Where's Wu Shixian?

304
00:21:38,060 --> 00:21:38,779
He finished a while ago.

305
00:21:39,060 --> 00:21:40,300
Do you want to check backstage?

306
00:21:40,439 --> 00:21:41,439
Alright.

307
00:21:44,840 --> 00:21:45,840
How do you explain this?

308
00:21:47,359 --> 00:21:48,960
That's not even me.

309
00:21:50,000 --> 00:21:51,579
Did you guys sleep together yesterday?

310
00:21:51,680 --> 00:21:52,819
I already told you,

311
00:21:53,479 --> 00:21:54,479
I'm not interested

312
00:21:54,579 --> 00:21:55,579
in men.

